8ff-4da5-810d-47ed930371bf", "question_text": "In the context of the lecture, what would be a suitable application of clustering in retail?", "question_type": "MULTIPLE_CHOICE", "student_answer": "", "correct_answer": "Segmenting customers into groups for targeted marketing.", "is_correct": false, "points_earned": 0, "points_possible": 1, "explanation": "Clustering can segment customers into groups like 'bargain hunters' for targeted marketing strategies.", "options": ["Identifying the best store locations based on traffic data.", "Segmenting customers into groups for targeted marketing.", "Predicting annual sales based on historical data.", "Developing a customer service chatbot."]}, {"question_id": "1fb9f721-a8af-4a8d-bdd5-5c4c3c82b004", "question_text": "When applying clustering algorithms to the California Housing Prices dataset, what is a potential benefit?", "question_type": "MULTIPLE_CHOICE", "student_answer": "", "correct_answer": "Identifying regions with similar market dynamics.", "is_correct": false, "points_earned": 0, "points_possible": 1, "explanation": "Clustering can group regions based on housing features to identify similar market dynamics.", "options": ["Predicting future housing prices with high accuracy.", "Identifying regions with similar market dynamics.", "Automatically setting house prices based on cluster assignment.", "Generating detailed legal property descriptions."]}, {"question_id": "925da783-6225-4f4c-9d50-9068b7e7b24f", "question_text": "What is a real-world example of document clustering?", "question_type": "MULTIPLE_CHOICE", "student_answer": "", "correct_answer": "Organizing news articles into categories like 'sports' and 'politics'.", "is_correct": false, "points_earned": 0, "points_possible": 1, "explanation": "Document clustering can automatically group articles into categories without manual tagging.", "options": ["Organizing news articles into categories like 'sports' and 'politics'.", "Predicting the popularity of articles based on past trends.", "Identifying fake news by comparing articles to known sources.", "Summarizing articles using natural language processing."]}, {"question_id": "04f0e413-c0dd-4cd7-90e2-50771b8d2199", "question_text": "Which of the following is true about hierarchical clustering?", "question_type": "MULTIPLE_CHOICE", "student_answer": "", "correct_answer": "It can be used to create a dendrogram representing data hierarchies.", "is_correct": false, "points_earned": 0, "points_possible": 1, "explanation": "Hierarchical clustering creates a dendrogram, showing the data's hierarchical relationships.", "options": ["It partitions data into clusters of equal size.", "It requires the number of clusters as an input parameter.", "It can be used to create a dendrogram representing data hierarchies.", "It is generally faster than K-Means for very large datasets."]}, {"question_id": "4ff22417-fe91-4a92-9efd-67b634bad54e", "question_text": "Why might a company use clustering to segment its customer base?", "question_type": "MULTIPLE_CHOICE", "student_answer": "", "correct_answer": "To tailor marketing strategies to different customer segments.", "is_correct": false, "points_earned": 0, "points_possible": 1, "explanation": "Clustering helps identify customer segments, allowing for more targeted and effective marketing strategies.", "options": ["To predict individual customer purchases.", "To prevent customer churn by identifying loyal customers.", "To tailor marketing strategies to different customer segments.", "To automate customer service interactions."]}, {"question_id": "1ac10342-6d86-4e3a-b15d-e2711dcf37fe", "question_text": "What role does the iterative process play in the K-Means algorithm?", "question_type": "MULTIPLE_CHOICE", "student_answer": "", "correct_answer": "It adjusts cluster centroids to minimize intra-cluster variance.", "is_correct": false, "points_earned": 0, "points_possible": 1, "explanation": "The iterative process in K-Means adjusts cluster centroids