umerical data.", "correct_answer": "They organize data into meaningful patterns without predefined labels.", "is_correct": false, "points_earned": 0, "points_possible": 1, "explanation": "Clustering is an unsupervised learning technique that organizes data without predefined labels.", "options": ["They require labeled datasets.", "They are primarily supervised learning techniques.", "They organize data into meaningful patterns without predefined labels.", "They are only applicable to numerical data."]}, {"question_id": "3154bcf4-a854-4cf8-a1a3-18247227ae40", "question_text": "How does hierarchical clustering differ from K-Means?", "question_type": "MULTIPLE_CHOICE", "student_answer": "Hierarchical clustering requires choosing the number of clusters beforehand.", "correct_answer": "Hierarchical clustering constructs a tree of clusters through successive merges.", "is_correct": false, "points_earned": 0, "points_possible": 1, "explanation": "Hierarchical clustering constructs a tree by merging clusters based on similarity until a single cluster is formed.", "options": ["Hierarchical clustering requires choosing the number of clusters beforehand.", "Hierarchical clustering builds a single cluster directly.", "Hierarchical clustering constructs a tree of clusters through successive merges.", "Hierarchical clustering is faster than K-Means for large datasets."]}, {"question_id": "ffc78c47-f63d-4e68-b142-2e086ea92e23", "question_text": "Why is clustering considered an unsupervised learning technique?", "question_type": "MULTIPLE_CHOICE", "student_answer": "It identifies patterns in data without explicit instructions or labels.", "correct_answer": "It identifies patterns in data without explicit instructions or labels.", "is_correct": true, "points_earned": 1, "points_possible": 1, "explanation": "Clustering is unsupervised because it finds patterns in data without using labeled outcomes.", "options": ["It uses labeled data to predict outcomes.", "It identifies patterns in data without explicit instructions or labels.", "It requires human intervention to group data.", "It organizes data based on pre-existing categories."]}, {"question_id": "99cb7813-98ff-4da5-810d-47ed930371bf", "question_text": "In the context of the lecture, what would be a suitable application of clustering in retail?", "question_type": "MULTIPLE_CHOICE", "student_answer": "Developing a customer service chatbot.", "correct_answer": "Segmenting customers into groups for targeted marketing.", "is_correct": false, "points_earned": 0, "points_possible": 1, "explanation": "Clustering can segment customers into groups like 'bargain hunters' for targeted marketing strategies.", "options": ["Identifying the best store locations based on traffic data.", "Segmenting customers into groups for targeted marketing.", "Predicting annual sales based on historical data.", "Developing a customer service chatbot."]}, {"question_id": "1fb9f721-a8af-4a8d-bdd5-5c4c3c82b004", "question_text": "When applying clustering algorithms to the California Housing Prices dataset, what is a potential benefit?", "question_type": "MULTIPLE_CHOICE", "student_answer": "Identifying regions with similar market dynamics.", "correct_answer": "Identifying regions with similar market dynamics.", "is_correct": true, "points_earned": 1, "points_possible": 1, "explanation": "Clustering can group regions based on housing features to identify similar market dynamics.", "options": ["Predicting future housing prices with high accuracy.", "Identifying regions with similar market dynamics.", "Automatically setting house prices based on cluster assignment.", "Generating detailed legal property descriptions."]}, {"question_id": "925da783-6225-4f4c-9d50-9068b7e7b24f", "question_text": "What is a real-world example of document clustering?", "question_type": "MULTIPLE_CHOICE", "student_answer": "Summarizing articles using natural language processing.", "correct_answer": "Organizing news articles into categories like 'sports' and 'politics'.", "is_correct": false, "points_earned": 0, "points_possible": 1, "explanation": "Document clustering can automatically group articles into categories without manual tagging.", "options": ["Organizing news articles into categories like 'sports' and 'politics'.", "Predicting the popularity of articles based on past trends.", "Identifying fake news by comparing articles to known sources.", "Summarizing articles using natural language processing."]}, {"question_id": "04f0e413-c0dd-4cd7-90e2-50771b8d2199", "question_text": "Which of the following is true about hierarchical clustering?", "question_type": "MULTIPLE_CHOICE", "student_answer": "It partitions data into clusters of equal size.", "correct_answer": "It can be used to create a dendrogram representing data hierarchies.", "is_correct": false, "points_earned": 0, "points_possible": 1, "explanation": "Hierarchical clustering creates a dendrogram, showing the data's hierarchical relationships.", "options": ["It partitions data into clusters of equal size.", "It requires the number of clusters as an input parameter.", "It can be used to create a dendrogram representing data hierarchies.", "It is generally faster than K-Means for very large datasets."]}, {"question_id": "4ff22417-fe91-4a92-9efd-67b634bad54e", "question_text": "Why might a company use clustering to segment its customer base?", "question_type": "MULTIPLE_CHOICE", "student_answer": "To predict individual customer purchases.", "correct_answer": "To tailor marketing strategies to different customer segments.", "is_correct": false, "points_earned": 0, "points_possible": 1, "explanation": "Clustering helps identify customer segments, allowing for more targeted and effective marketing strategies.", "options": ["To predict individual customer purchases.", "To prevent customer churn by identifying loyal customers.", "To tailor marketing strategies to different customer segments.", "To automate customer service interactions."]}, {"question_id": "1ac10342-6d86-4e3a-b15d-e2711dcf37fe", "question_text": "What role does the iterative process play in the K-Means algorithm?", "question_type": "MULTIPLE_CHOICE", "student_answer": "It adjusts cluster centroids to minimize intra-cluster variance.", "correct_answer": "It adjusts cluster centroids to minimize intra-cluster variance.", "is_correct": true, "points_earned": 1, "points_possible": 1, "explanation": "The iterative process in K-Means adjusts cluster centroids to minimize the variance within clusters.", "options": ["It gradually reduces the number of clusters in the dataset.", "It adjusts cluster centroids to minimize intra-cluster variance.", "It helps in assigning categorical labels to numerical data.", "It arranges data into hierarchical tiers over several passes."]}]}	2025-11-27 10:13:46.258906
