982b2e06-2391-43ee-8cac-7e6553c266e7	338d3884-6e46-4236-8d9e-d9bd82619336	SYSTEM	Quiz Results:\n- Score: 8/10 (80.0%)\n- Questions Correct: 8/10\n- Topics to Review: Which case established that a..., In the case of electronic...\n\nI'm here to help you understand any topics you found challenging. Feel free to ask questions about: Which case established that a..., In the case of electronic....	{"assessment_id": "6fd89164-e8b5-4baf-bbf9-f89c127e8e00", "submission_id": "86803e01-c1c9-4f6a-815b-c05cf36f3467", "score": 8, "max_score": 10, "percentage": 80.0, "weak_areas": ["Which case established that a...", "In the case of electronic..."], "question_results": [{"question_id": "fc2303f2-061f-45c2-90ff-a850ce32bccd", "question_text": "Which of the following scenarios best illustrates an invitation to treat?", "question_type": "MULTIPLE_CHOICE", "student_answer": "A restaurant menu listing prices for each dish.", "correct_answer": "A restaurant menu listing prices for each dish.", "is_correct": true, "points_earned": 1, "points_possible": 1, "explanation": "A menu price is generally an invitation to treat, meaning it invites customers to make an offer to purchase.", "options": ["A restaurant menu listing prices for each dish.", "A customer offering to buy a car for $10,000.", "An advertisement stating 'first come, first served'.", "A store employee saying, 'I will sell this to you for $50.'"]}, {"question_id": "2cee04db-6283-46d9-a26a-d82c6696b7df", "question_text": "What is the primary distinction between a bilateral and a unilateral contract?", "question_type": "MULTIPLE_CHOICE", "student_answer": "A bilateral contract involves a promise in exchange for a promise.", "correct_answer": "A bilateral contract involves a promise in exchange for a promise.", "is_correct": true, "points_earned": 1, "points_possible": 1, "explanation": "In a bilateral contract, both parties make promises to each other, unlike a unilateral contract which involves a promise in exchange for an act.", "options": ["A bilateral contract requires only one party to make a promise.", "A unilateral contract is formed when both parties make promises.", "A bilateral contract involves a promise in exchange for a promise.", "A unilateral contract involves a promise in exchange for a promise."]}, {"question_id": "26b4d37e-6b05-4f2a-b925-97a5588f45f3", "question_text": "Which case established that a counter-offer nullifies the original offer?", "question_type": "MULTIPLE_CHOICE", "student_answer": "Errington v Errington", "correct_answer": "Hyde v Wrench", "is_correct": false, "points_earned": 0, "points_possible": 1, "explanation": "Hyde v Wrench established that a counter-offer nullifies the original offer, as it does not mirror the original terms.", "options": ["Carlill v Carbolic Smoke Ball Co", "Hyde v Wrench", "Partridge v Crittenden", "Errington v Errington"]}, {"question_id": "aa025e36-d8c9-4f48-a39f-1e77a89ae0d9", "question_text": "How does the postal rule affect the timing of acceptance?", "question_type": "MULTIPLE_CHOICE", "student_answer": "Acceptance is effective when the letter is posted.", "correct_answer": "Acceptance is effective when the letter is posted.", "is_correct": true, "points_earned": 1, "points_possible": 1, "explanation": "The postal rule states that acceptance is complete once the acceptance letter is posted, not when it is received.", "options": ["Acceptance is effective when the letter is written.", "Acceptance is effective when the offeror receives the letter.", "Acceptance is effective when the letter is posted.", "Acceptance is effective when the letter is delivered."]}, {"question_id": "d18eec51-07cf-432c-bca8-cc99784ec107", "question_text": "In the case of electronic communications, when is acceptance effective?", "question_type": "MULTIPLE_CHOICE", "student_answer": "When the acceptance email is sent.", "correct_answer": "When the acceptance email is received by the offeror.", "is_correct": false, "points_earned": 0, "points_possible": 1, "explanation": "For electronic communications, acceptance is effective when it is received by the offeror, not when it is sent.", "options": ["When the acceptance email is sent.", "When the acceptance email is received by the offeror.", "When the acceptance email is read by the offeree.", "When the acceptance email is received by the offeree."]}, {"question_id": "701ae6bf-c025-420b-86aa-2004db301c9b", "question_text": "Why is the mirror image rule important in contract law?", "question_type": "MULTIPLE_CHOICE", "student_answer": "It ensures both parties have agreed to the same terms without modifications.", "correct_answer": "It ensures both parties have agreed to the same terms without modifications.", "is_correct": true, "points_earned": 1, "points_possible": 1, "explanation": "The mirror image rule ensures clarity and mutual agreement by requiring the acceptance to exactly match the offer.", "options": ["It ensures both parties are flexible in their terms.", "It allows for one-sided alterations to the contract.", "It ensures both parties have agreed to the same terms without modifications.", "It prevents any acceptance from being binding."]}, {"question_id": "6f5af2d3-03a6-4328-bbac-137f869241cc", "question_text": "Which of the following is true about the revocation of offers?", "question_type": "MULTIPLE_CHOICE", "student_answer": "Offers can be revoked anytime before acceptance is communicated.", "correct_answer": "Offers can be revoked anytime before acceptance is communicated.", "is_correct": true, "points_earned": 1, "points_possible": 1, "explanation": "Offers can generally be revoked any time before the offeree communicates acceptance, but revocation must be communicated to the offeree.", "options": ["Offers can be revoked at any time, even after acceptance.", "Offers can be revoked anytime before acceptance is communicated.", "Offers in unilateral contracts can always be revoked after performance begins.", "Communication of revocation is unnecessary for it to be effective."]}, {"question_id": "da57dbcd-01c8-488d-a80e-bc2056ea82c2", "question_text": "In the case of a reward contract, when does acceptance occur?", "question_type": "MULTIPLE_CHOICE", "student_answer": "Upon the successful performance of the requested act.", "correct_answer": "Upon the successful performance of the requested act.", "is_correct": true, "points_earned": 1, "points_possible": 1, "explanation": "In a unilateral contract, like a reward, acceptance occurs when the requested act is performed.", "options": ["When the offeree promises to find the lost item.", "When the offeree informs the offeror of their intention to perform.", "Upon the successful performance of the requested act.", "When the offeror gives the reward."]}, {"question_id": "cfebba62-74fb-4659-9899-eb9847efca6e", "question_text": "How does the case of *Carlill v Carbolic Smoke Ball Co* illustrate a unilateral contract?", "question_type": "MULTIPLE_CHOICE", "student_answer": "The company promised payment upon the performance of an act (using the product).", "correct_answer": "The company promised payment upon the performance of an act (using the product).", "is_correct": true, "points_earned": 1, "points_possible": 1, "explanation": "*Carlill v Carbolic Smoke Ball Co* is a classic unilateral contract case where the company promised payment upon the act of using their product.", "options": ["It involved a promise of payment upon selling a product.", "The company promised payment upon the performance of an act (using the product).", "It was based on mutual promises between two parties.", "It involved a counter-offer that was accepted."]}, {"question_id": "55bcd07c-a1b0-4921-8d07-c5287056c57e", "question_text": "What principle was suggested by Lord Denning regarding the revocation of unilateral offers in *Errington v Errington*?", "question_type": "MULTIPLE_CHOICE", "student_answer": "Once performance has started, the offer cannot be revoked.", "correct_answer": "Once performance has started, the offer cannot be revoked.", "is_correct": true, "points_earned": 1, "points_possible": 1, "explanation": "Lord Denning suggested that in a unilateral contract, once the offeree has begun performance, the offeror cannot revoke the offer.", "options": ["Unilateral offers can be revoked at any time.", "Performance must begin before a revocation can be effective.", "Once performance has started, the offer cannot be revoked.", "Revocation is effective without communication."]}]}	2025-11-27 11:21:54.567373
