COPY public.question (id, assessment_id, question_text, question_type, points, order_index, options, correct_answer, explanation, created_at, updated_at) FROM stdin;
4ef65f8e-e7ff-4c59-8396-3b4d1e23ad3b	87599146-cba8-4a82-9735-f13e9e0a9253	Which of the following best describes the K-Means algorithm?	MULTIPLE_CHOICE	1	0	["It organizes data into a tree structure based on distance.", "It assigns data points to clusters to minimize inter-cluster distance.", "It requires predefined labels for data classification.", "It uses decision trees to classify data without clusters."]	It assigns data points to clusters to minimize inter-cluster distance.	K-Means assigns data points to clusters to minimize the distance between points and their cluster centers.	2025-11-03 07:54:09.34887	2025-11-03 07:54:09.34887
18aec2af-0c1d-4e5c-8393-1b0693da32bd	87599146-cba8-4a82-9735-f13e9e0a9253	What is a key characteristic of clustering algorithms?	MULTIPLE_CHOICE	1	1	["They require labeled datasets.", "They are primarily supervised learning techniques.", "They organize data into meaningful patterns without predefined labels.", "They are only applicable to numerical data."]	They organize data into meaningful patterns without predefined labels.	Clustering is an unsupervised learning technique that organizes data without predefined labels.	2025-11-03 07:54:09.34887	2025-11-03 07:54:09.34887
3154bcf4-a854-4cf8-a1a3-18247227ae40	87599146-cba8-4a82-9735-f13e9e0a9253	How does hierarchical clustering differ from K-Means?	MULTIPLE_CHOICE	1	2	["Hierarchical clustering requires choosing the number of clusters beforehand.", "Hierarchical clustering builds a single cluster directly.", "Hierarchical clustering constructs a tree of clusters through successive merges.", "Hierarchical clustering is faster than K-Means for large datasets."]	Hierarchical clustering constructs a tree of clusters through successive merges.	Hierarchical clustering constructs a tree by merging clusters based on similarity until a single cluster is formed.	2025-11-03 07:54:09.34887	2025-11-03 07:54:09.34887
fcb53851-8d5d-4d1d-b64d-2537026f3bcf	ee4297bc-ae19-4e8e-b53e-8c207fda4177	Which ethical standard is NOT mentioned as a key for lawyers in the lecture?	MULTIPLE_CHOICE	1	4	["Integrity", "Loyalty", "Independence", "Fairness"]	Loyalty	Integrity, independence, and fairness are highlighted, but loyalty is not mentioned as a key standard.	2025-11-27 17:20:03.950923	2025-11-27 17:20:03.950923
3013542c-5c25-4d23-be5f-f0342dd0ab6b	ee4297bc-ae19-4e8e-b53e-8c207fda4177	What is the analogy used in the lecture to describe the role of lawyers?	MULTIPLE_CHOICE	1	5	["Doctors diagnosing patients", "Lighthouses in a storm", "Teachers guiding students", "Bridges connecting communities"]	Lighthouses in a storm	Lawyers are compared to lighthouses guiding ships safely to shore.	2025-11-27 17:20:03.950923	2025-11-27 17:20:03.950923
e32e16aa-53ae-46d9-a599-9d571a06440b	ee4297bc-ae19-4e8e-b53e-8c207fda4177	Which skill is NOT emphasized as essential for future legal professionals in the lecture?	MULTIPLE_CHOICE	1	6	["Attention to detail", "Punctuality", "Creativity", "Professionalism"]	Creativity	The lecture emphasizes attention to detail, punctuality, and professionalism, but not creativity.	2025-11-27 17:20:03.950923	2025-11-27 17:20:03.950923
ba5227f7-505e-479a-8a87-c0f5106511a0	ee4297bc-ae19-4e8e-b53e-8c207fda4177	How should students engage with the course material according to the lecture?	MULTIPLE_CHOICE	1	7	["Passively absorb information", "Actively engage and take ownership", "Merely focus on memorization", "Rely on lectures only"]	Actively engage and take ownership	Students are encouraged to actively engage with the material and take ownership of their learning journey.	2025-11-27 17:20:03.950923	2025-11-27 17:20:03.950923
d4efa269-98f4-4744-9ad0-94ea4dcf2503	ee4297bc-ae19-4e8e-b53e-8c207fda4177	In the lecture, how are lawyers compared to doctors?	MULTIPLE_CHOICE	1	8	["Both diagnose and treat conditions", "Both guide clients through complex processes", "Both work in life-saving professions", "Both are required to take oaths"]	Both guide clients through complex processes	Lawyers, like doctors, guide clients through complex processes with skill and integrity.	2025-11-27 17:20:03.950923	2025-11-27 17:20:03.950923
8a2d3d59-7cc9-42ac-9ff5-936571d58248	ee4297bc-ae19-4e8e-b53e-8c207fda4177	What critical thinking aspect is emphasized for lawyers in the lecture?	MULTIPLE_CHOICE	1	9	["Ability to memorize laws", "Capacity for thorough research and analysis", "Skill in negotiation", "Proficiency in public speaking"]	Capacity for thorough research and analysis	The lecture emphasizes the capacity for thorough research and critical analysis as key for lawyers.	2025-11-27 17:20:03.950923	2025-11-27 17:20:03.950923
5a410c2c-004f-42df-9ee2-518f94982896	cb9182ef-a171-4f5b-8873-3fe97087c298	What is one of the earliest known legal codes, originating around 1760 BC?	MULTIPLE_CHOICE	1	0	["The Twelve Tables", "The Code of Hammurabi", "The Napoleonic Code", "Corpus Juris Civilis"]	The Code of Hammurabi	The Code of Hammurabi is one of the earliest known legal codes, dating back to ancient Mesopotamia.	2025-11-27 17:35:05.444024	2025-11-27 17:35:05.444024
5e04a2cb-5260-412c-9513-fd6f097a7f1f	cb9182ef-a171-4f5b-8873-3fe97087c298	Which Athenian statesman introduced reforms in the 6th century BC to address social and economic crises?	MULTIPLE_CHOICE	1	1	["Pericles", "Cleisthenes", "Solon", "Lycurgus"]	Solon	Solon was an Athenian statesman who introduced significant legal reforms to stabilize Athens.	2025-11-27 17:35:05.444024	2025-11-27 17:35:05.444024
b6230cd6-1ad0-41b9-a99c-a37e157dbbdb	cb9182ef-a171-4f5b-8873-3fe97087c298	What was the significance of the Twelve Tables in Roman law?	MULTIPLE_CHOICE	1	2	["It was the first code to address trade laws", "It aimed to resolve disputes among citizens", "It was the basis of the Napoleonic Code", "It provided guidelines for legal professionals only"]	It aimed to resolve disputes among citizens	The Twelve Tables were designed to make laws accessible and help resolve disputes among Roman citizens.	2025-11-27 17:35:05.444024	2025-11-27 17:35:05.444024
3ea70de6-a2a9-4f53-a36d-c465adb32608	cb9182ef-a171-4f5b-8873-3fe97087c298	What was Emperor Justinian's contribution to the legal system?	MULTIPLE_CHOICE	1	3	["He created the first common law system", "He codified Roman law into the Corpus Juris Civilis", "He established the first legal university", "He wrote a legal manual for judges"]	He codified Roman law into the Corpus Juris Civilis	Emperor Justinian codified Roman law into the Corpus Juris Civilis, which became a foundational legal resource.	2025-11-27 17:35:05.444024	2025-11-27 17:35:05.444024
31a0edd9-95b6-4417-8ae5-211e45463f27	cb9182ef-a171-4f5b-8873-3fe97087c298	What is a distinctive feature of the Western legal tradition?	MULTIPLE_CHOICE	1	4	["Emphasis on oral traditions", "Clear separation between legal and political institutions", "Reliance solely on religious texts", "Use of tribal councils for dispute resolution"]	Clear separation between legal and political institutions	The Western legal tradition emphasizes a clear separation between legal and political institutions, ensuring rule of law.	2025-11-27 17:35:05.444024	2025-11-27 17:35:05.444024
04c0875e-8225-4af2-9235-15d304477b81	cb9182ef-a171-4f5b-8873-3fe97087c298	How does common law primarily evolve?	MULTIPLE_CHOICE	1	5	["Through legislative statutes", "By judicial decisions and case law", "By executive orders", "Based on historical customs"]	By judicial decisions and case law	Common law evolves through judicial decisions and case law, which build upon previous court rulings.	2025-11-27 17:35:05.444024	2025-11-27 17:35:05.444024
8a0d40d4-5af9-4407-ab12-b6ef0ec71381	cb9182ef-a171-4f5b-8873-3fe97087c298	What is a key difference between common law and civil law systems?	MULTIPLE_CHOICE	1	6	["Common law uses codified statutes, civil law does not", "Civil law is based on case law, common law is not", "Common law relies on judicial decisions, civil law on codified statutes", "Both systems use the same approach but differ in language"]	Common law relies on judicial decisions, civil law on codified statutes	Common law relies on judicial decisions to evolve, while civil law is based on detailed codified statutes.	2025-11-27 17:35:05.444024	2025-11-27 17:35:05.444024
ffc78c47-f63d-4e68-b142-2e086ea92e23	87599146-cba8-4a82-9735-f13e9e0a9253	Why is clustering considered an unsupervised learning technique?	MULTIPLE_CHOICE	1	3	["It uses labeled data to predict outcomes.", "It identifies patterns in data without explicit instructions or labels.", "It requires human intervention to group data.", "It organizes data based on pre-existing categories."]	It identifies patterns in data without explicit instructions or labels.	Clustering is unsupervised because it finds patterns in data without using labeled outcomes.	2025-11-03 07:54:09.34887	2025-11-03 07:54:09.34887
99cb7813-98ff-4da5-810d-47ed930371bf	87599146-cba8-4a82-9735-f13e9e0a9253	In the context of the lecture, what would be a suitable application of clustering in retail?	MULTIPLE_CHOICE	1	4	["Identifying the best store locations based on traffic data.", "Segmenting customers into groups for targeted marketing.", "Predicting annual sales based on historical data.", "Developing a customer service chatbot."]	Segmenting customers into groups for targeted marketing.	Clustering can segment customers into groups like 'bargain hunters' for targeted marketing strategies.	2025-11-03 07:54:09.34887	2025-11-03 07:54:09.34887
1fb9f721-a8af-4a8d-bdd5-5c4c3c82b004	87599146-cba8-4a82-9735-f13e9e0a9253	When applying clustering algorithms to the California Housing Prices dataset, what is a potential benefit?	MULTIPLE_CHOICE	1	5	["Predicting future housing prices with high accuracy.", "Identifying regions with similar market dynamics.", "Automatically setting house prices based on cluster assignment.", "Generating detailed legal property descriptions."]	Identifying regions with similar market dynamics.	Clustering can group regions based on housing features to identify similar market dynamics.	2025-11-03 07:54:09.34887	2025-11-03 07:54:09.34887
925da783-6225-4f4c-9d50-9068b7e7b24f	87599146-cba8-4a82-9735-f13e9e0a9253	What is a real-world example of document clustering?	MULTIPLE_CHOICE	1	6	["Organizing news articles into categories like 'sports' and 'politics'.", "Predicting the popularity of articles based on past trends.", "Identifying fake news by comparing articles to known sources.", "Summarizing articles using natural language processing."]	Organizing news articles into categories like 'sports' and 'politics'.	Document clustering can automatically group articles into categories without manual tagging.	2025-11-03 07:54:09.34887	2025-11-03 07:54:09.34887
04f0e413-c0dd-4cd7-90e2-50771b8d2199	87599146-cba8-4a82-9735-f13e9e0a9253	Which of the following is true about hierarchical clustering?	MULTIPLE_CHOICE	1	7	["It partitions data into clusters of equal size.", "It requires the number of clusters as an input parameter.", "It can be used to create a dendrogram representing data hierarchies.", "It is generally faster than K-Means for very large datasets."]	It can be used to create a dendrogram representing data hierarchies.	Hierarchical clustering creates a dendrogram, showing the data's hierarchical relationships.	2025-11-03 07:54:09.34887	2025-11-03 07:54:09.34887
4ff22417-fe91-4a92-9efd-67b634bad54e	87599146-cba8-4a82-9735-f13e9e0a9253	Why might a company use clustering to segment its customer base?	MULTIPLE_CHOICE	1	8	["To predict individual customer purchases.", "To prevent customer churn by identifying loyal customers.", "To tailor marketing strategies to different customer segments.", "To automate customer service interactions."]	To tailor marketing strategies to different customer segments.	Clustering helps identify customer segments, allowing for more targeted and effective marketing strategies.	2025-11-03 07:54:09.34887	2025-11-03 07:54:09.34887
1ac10342-6d86-4e3a-b15d-e2711dcf37fe	87599146-cba8-4a82-9735-f13e9e0a9253	What role does the iterative process play in the K-Means algorithm?	MULTIPLE_CHOICE	1	9	["It gradually reduces the number of clusters in the dataset.", "It adjusts cluster centroids to minimize intra-cluster variance.", "It helps in assigning categorical labels to numerical data.", "It arranges data into hierarchical tiers over several passes."]	It adjusts cluster centroids to minimize intra-cluster variance.	The iterative process in K-Means adjusts cluster centroids to minimize the variance within clusters.	2025-11-03 07:54:09.34887	2025-11-03 07:54:09.34887
be57460d-1ed9-4ed7-b876-7b1286e2dd51	9e57b612-ad50-4bac-a452-8ec02c7ec214	Which learning algorithm is described as the agent learning directly from interactions without a model of the environment?	MULTIPLE_CHOICE	1	3	["Model-Based Learning", "Q-Learning", "Supervised Learning", "Unsupervised Learning"]	Q-Learning	Q-Learning is a type of model-free learning where the agent learns the value of actions directly from interactions with the environment.	2025-11-27 10:32:22.726846	2025-11-27 10:32:22.726849
ea5d0041-9118-4946-bfc4-f5f9e321cac0	1e5b273d-7ba2-41fa-87b7-182bd31aa14b	What is often considered the foundational purpose of individual rights and liberties?	MULTIPLE_CHOICE	1	0	["To ensure state sovereignty", "To promote economic growth", "To provide a dignified life for all", "To limit technological advancement"]	To provide a dignified life for all	Individual rights and liberties are fundamental for ensuring freedom, justice, and peace, providing the minimum standards necessary for a dignified life.	2025-11-27 09:48:36.840417	2025-11-27 09:48:36.840425
e208b261-e281-42ff-9e18-5697de59c45f	1e5b273d-7ba2-41fa-87b7-182bd31aa14b	Which international document serves as a moral compass for global human rights?	MULTIPLE_CHOICE	1	1	["The Magna Carta", "The Universal Declaration of Human Rights", "The European Convention on Human Rights", "The Geneva Conventions"]	The Universal Declaration of Human Rights	The Universal Declaration of Human Rights, proclaimed in 1948, acts as a global benchmark for human dignity despite not being legally binding.	2025-11-27 09:48:36.840441	2025-11-27 09:48:36.840443
71b4f58b-575c-4a9b-881b-cb5e1d65d180	1e5b273d-7ba2-41fa-87b7-182bd31aa14b	Why might some countries hesitate to implement international human rights standards?	MULTIPLE_CHOICE	1	2	["Because they are already financially stable", "Due to cultural, political, and economic factors", "Because they prioritize technology", "Due to lack of awareness"]	Due to cultural, political, and economic factors	Countries might hesitate due to cultural, political, and economic factors that affect their ability to fully adopt international standards.	2025-11-27 09:48:36.840454	2025-11-27 09:48:36.840455
286f71d2-2511-45d8-95a4-6c092509fde3	1e5b273d-7ba2-41fa-87b7-182bd31aa14b	What makes the European Convention on Human Rights (ECHR) significant compared to the UDHR?	MULTIPLE_CHOICE	1	3	["It's older than the UDHR", "It is legally binding for member states", "It focuses only on economic rights", "It was drafted by the United Nations"]	It is legally binding for member states	The ECHR is significant because it is a legally binding treaty that obligates member states to uphold its principles.	2025-11-27 09:48:36.840464	2025-11-27 09:48:36.840465
e02c2ca7-233f-45ee-a7ed-7b007f57de0f	1e5b273d-7ba2-41fa-87b7-182bd31aa14b	In the context of law, how are human rights compared?	MULTIPLE_CHOICE	1	4	["As a national constitution", "As a set of localized rules", "As an international constitution", "As economic guidelines"]	As an international constitution	Human rights are likened to an international constitution, setting standards that transcend borders and apply universally.	2025-11-27 09:48:36.840474	2025-11-27 09:48:36.840475
d3f064cc-4b62-46f7-b9e9-c4c61fcef491	1e5b273d-7ba2-41fa-87b7-182bd31aa14b	What is a major challenge of enforcing international human rights?	MULTIPLE_CHOICE	1	5	["Lack of public interest", "Absence of global enforcement mechanisms", "Overabundance of treaties", "Conflict with economic growth strategies"]	Absence of global enforcement mechanisms	International human rights face challenges in enforcement due to the lack of mechanisms similar to those in national laws.	2025-11-27 09:48:36.840484	2025-11-27 09:48:36.840485
c3b5c02c-9108-43b8-b342-2b28813cbe36	1e5b273d-7ba2-41fa-87b7-182bd31aa14b	Which case exemplifies the conflict between religious freedom and state law?	MULTIPLE_CHOICE	1	6	["Zaheeruddin v The State", "Brown v Board of Education", "Roe v Wade", "Marbury v Madison"]	Zaheeruddin v The State	Zaheeruddin v The State is a case from Pakistan that highlights the conflict between religious freedoms and state laws.	2025-11-27 09:48:36.840492	2025-11-27 09:48:36.840493
2409aacd-0180-4cdc-a156-dccb5f7fbe03	1e5b273d-7ba2-41fa-87b7-182bd31aa14b	What is a core principle of human rights intended to ensure?	MULTIPLE_CHOICE	1	7	["Economic equality", "Universal and uniform application", "Cultural diversity", "Technological advancement"]	Universal and uniform application	Human rights are designed to be universal and uniform, applying to everyone, everywhere, to ensure fairness and dignity.	2025-11-27 09:48:36.840501	2025-11-27 09:48:36.840502
4a064a98-38ee-4927-a07d-462382cd3757	1e5b273d-7ba2-41fa-87b7-182bd31aa14b	What can influence a state's decision to enforce international human rights laws?	MULTIPLE_CHOICE	1	8	["Cultural exchanges", "International pressure or support", "Domestic economic challenges", "Technological advancements"]	International pressure or support	A state's decision to enforce international human rights laws can be influenced by international pressure or support.	2025-11-27 09:48:36.840509	2025-11-27 09:48:36.84051
c0979081-2421-4378-b3f7-4725471e6039	1e5b273d-7ba2-41fa-87b7-182bd31aa14b	How does the UDHR continue to impact human rights development?	MULTIPLE_CHOICE	1	9	["By being legally binding", "Through cultural influence", "As a historical benchmark", "By enforcing compliance"]	As a historical benchmark	The UDHR remains significant as a historical benchmark, influencing the ongoing development of human rights worldwide.	2025-11-27 09:48:36.840518	2025-11-27 09:48:36.840518
e046bd9d-e34d-441f-b9b9-0d04404dcdbc	9e57b612-ad50-4bac-a452-8ec02c7ec214	What distinguishes reinforcement learning from supervised and unsupervised learning?	MULTIPLE_CHOICE	1	0	["It relies on labeled datasets to learn", "It involves discovering hidden patterns in data", "It learns by interacting with an environment to maximize cumulative reward", "It primarily uses static datasets for model training"]	It learns by interacting with an environment to maximize cumulative reward	Reinforcement learning is unique because it learns by interacting with the environment, unlike supervised learning, which uses labeled data, or unsupervised learning, which seeks patterns.	2025-11-27 10:32:22.726749	2025-11-27 10:32:22.726762
68d3caf3-f904-4efd-8f9e-5c660cfc847e	9e57b612-ad50-4bac-a452-8ec02c7ec214	Which component of reinforcement learning represents the current situation or context the agent is in?	MULTIPLE_CHOICE	1	1	["Agent", "Environment", "State", "Reward"]	State	The state represents the current situation the agent is in, which helps the agent decide what action to take.	2025-11-27 10:32:22.726784	2025-11-27 10:32:22.726787
fcd8a98d-d43e-42a8-8b6f-67d1ddc672ad	9e57b612-ad50-4bac-a452-8ec02c7ec214	Why is it essential to have a balance between exploration and exploitation in reinforcement learning?	MULTIPLE_CHOICE	1	2	["To ensure the agent always chooses the safest action", "To allow the agent to discover new strategies while using known successful actions", "To guarantee the agent only explores new actions", "To make sure the agent avoids any risky moves"]	To allow the agent to discover new strategies while using known successful actions	Balancing exploration and exploitation is crucial as it helps the agent discover potentially better actions while also using actions that have previously led to high rewards.	2025-11-27 10:32:22.726807	2025-11-27 10:32:22.726809
41a546e3-4f1b-43af-8fca-679c7146a78b	9e57b612-ad50-4bac-a452-8ec02c7ec214	In the context of reinforcement learning, what is a 'policy'?	MULTIPLE_CHOICE	1	4	["A set of rules governing the environment", "A mapping from states to actions that dictates the best action to take", "The feedback mechanism for the agent", "The strategy used to label data in supervised learning"]	A mapping from states to actions that dictates the best action to take	A policy is a strategy used by the agent to decide actions based on the states it encounters, with the goal of maximizing rewards.	2025-11-27 10:32:22.726869	2025-11-27 10:32:22.726872
f6e35133-1cbe-419f-9dbe-2165c366ffc7	9e57b612-ad50-4bac-a452-8ec02c7ec214	How might poorly designed reward structures lead to unintended behaviors in reinforcement learning?	MULTIPLE_CHOICE	1	5	["They can encourage the agent to explore more", "They might cause the agent to focus on short-term rewards over long-term goals", "They ensure the agent learns the optimal policy", "They make the agent ignore its environment"]	They might cause the agent to focus on short-term rewards over long-term goals	If the reward structure is not aligned with the desired outcomes, the agent might develop strategies that maximize short-term rewards, neglecting long-term objectives.	2025-11-27 10:32:22.72689	2025-11-27 10:32:22.726893
42d9b153-3161-48e9-b69b-5b50ff8aea12	9e57b612-ad50-4bac-a452-8ec02c7ec214	In which scenario might model-based learning be more advantageous than model-free learning?	MULTIPLE_CHOICE	1	6	["Where the environment is highly unpredictable", "When computational resources are limited", "In environments where the agent can simulate scenarios effectively", "When learning must occur in real-time"]	In environments where the agent can simulate scenarios effectively	Model-based learning is beneficial when the agent can use a model to simulate and plan its actions before executing them in the real environment.	2025-11-27 10:32:22.726913	2025-11-27 10:32:22.726916
c93e341e-e54c-44e3-b0af-160d8cd378f0	9e57b612-ad50-4bac-a452-8ec02c7ec214	What is one major challenge reinforcement learning faces in real-world applications?	MULTIPLE_CHOICE	1	7	["Lack of theoretical basis", "Curse of dimensionality", "Inability to handle sequential decision-making", "Finding labeled datasets"]	Curse of dimensionality	The 'curse of dimensionality' refers to the exponential increase in complexity as the state and action spaces grow, making it challenging to efficiently learn policies.	2025-11-27 10:32:22.726928	2025-11-27 10:32:22.726929
26cde7ee-8032-43aa-b77c-ba3799006470	9e57b612-ad50-4bac-a452-8ec02c7ec214	Which of the following is an example of a real-world application of reinforcement learning?	MULTIPLE_CHOICE	1	8	["Image classification", "Spam detection", "Self-driving cars", "Market basket analysis"]	Self-driving cars	Self-driving cars use reinforcement learning to learn complex driving tasks by interacting with simulated environments to improve decision-making.	2025-11-27 10:32:22.726942	2025-11-27 10:32:22.726943
26916228-62c0-468b-aa0c-9346dc9f5728	9e57b612-ad50-4bac-a452-8ec02c7ec214	How might advancements in technology like quantum computing impact reinforcement learning?	MULTIPLE_CHOICE	1	9	["By replacing the need for reinforcement learning", "By making the learning process slower", "By significantly enhancing computational power and efficiency", "By reducing the need for exploration"]	By significantly enhancing computational power and efficiency	Quantum computing could greatly increase computational power, allowing for more efficient processing and learning of complex models in reinforcement learning.	2025-11-27 10:32:22.726958	2025-11-27 10:32:22.72696
fc2303f2-061f-45c2-90ff-a850ce32bccd	6fd89164-e8b5-4baf-bbf9-f89c127e8e00	Which of the following scenarios best illustrates an invitation to treat?	MULTIPLE_CHOICE	1	0	["A restaurant menu listing prices for each dish.", "A customer offering to buy a car for $10,000.", "An advertisement stating 'first come, first served'.", "A store employee saying, 'I will sell this to you for $50.'"]	A restaurant menu listing prices for each dish.	A menu price is generally an invitation to treat, meaning it invites customers to make an offer to purchase.	2025-11-27 11:18:04.365933	2025-11-27 11:18:04.365946
2cee04db-6283-46d9-a26a-d82c6696b7df	6fd89164-e8b5-4baf-bbf9-f89c127e8e00	What is the primary distinction between a bilateral and a unilateral contract?	MULTIPLE_CHOICE	1	1	["A bilateral contract requires only one party to make a promise.", "A unilateral contract is formed when both parties make promises.", "A bilateral contract involves a promise in exchange for a promise.", "A unilateral contract involves a promise in exchange for a promise."]	A bilateral contract involves a promise in exchange for a promise.	In a bilateral contract, both parties make promises to each other, unlike a unilateral contract which involves a promise in exchange for an act.	2025-11-27 11:18:04.365967	2025-11-27 11:18:04.365969
26b4d37e-6b05-4f2a-b925-97a5588f45f3	6fd89164-e8b5-4baf-bbf9-f89c127e8e00	Which case established that a counter-offer nullifies the original offer?	MULTIPLE_CHOICE	1	2	["Carlill v Carbolic Smoke Ball Co", "Hyde v Wrench", "Partridge v Crittenden", "Errington v Errington"]	Hyde v Wrench	Hyde v Wrench established that a counter-offer nullifies the original offer, as it does not mirror the original terms.	2025-11-27 11:18:04.365984	2025-11-27 11:18:04.365986
aa025e36-d8c9-4f48-a39f-1e77a89ae0d9	6fd89164-e8b5-4baf-bbf9-f89c127e8e00	How does the postal rule affect the timing of acceptance?	MULTIPLE_CHOICE	1	3	["Acceptance is effective when the letter is written.", "Acceptance is effective when the offeror receives the letter.", "Acceptance is effective when the letter is posted.", "Acceptance is effective when the letter is delivered."]	Acceptance is effective when the letter is posted.	The postal rule states that acceptance is complete once the acceptance letter is posted, not when it is received.	2025-11-27 11:18:04.366	2025-11-27 11:18:04.366002
d18eec51-07cf-432c-bca8-cc99784ec107	6fd89164-e8b5-4baf-bbf9-f89c127e8e00	In the case of electronic communications, when is acceptance effective?	MULTIPLE_CHOICE	1	4	["When the acceptance email is sent.", "When the acceptance email is received by the offeror.", "When the acceptance email is read by the offeree.", "When the acceptance email is received by the offeree."]	When the acceptance email is received by the offeror.	For electronic communications, acceptance is effective when it is received by the offeror, not when it is sent.	2025-11-27 11:18:04.366016	2025-11-27 11:18:04.366018
701ae6bf-c025-420b-86aa-2004db301c9b	6fd89164-e8b5-4baf-bbf9-f89c127e8e00	Why is the mirror image rule important in contract law?	MULTIPLE_CHOICE	1	5	["It ensures both parties are flexible in their terms.", "It allows for one-sided alterations to the contract.", "It ensures both parties have agreed to the same terms without modifications.", "It prevents any acceptance from being binding."]	It ensures both parties have agreed to the same terms without modifications.	The mirror image rule ensures clarity and mutual agreement by requiring the acceptance to exactly match the offer.	2025-11-27 11:18:04.366034	2025-11-27 11:18:04.366036
6f5af2d3-03a6-4328-bbac-137f869241cc	6fd89164-e8b5-4baf-bbf9-f89c127e8e00	Which of the following is true about the revocation of offers?	MULTIPLE_CHOICE	1	6	["Offers can be revoked at any time, even after acceptance.", "Offers can be revoked anytime before acceptance is communicated.", "Offers in unilateral contracts can always be revoked after performance begins.", "Communication of revocation is unnecessary for it to be effective."]	Offers can be revoked anytime before acceptance is communicated.	Offers can generally be revoked any time before the offeree communicates acceptance, but revocation must be communicated to the offeree.	2025-11-27 11:18:04.36605	2025-11-27 11:18:04.366052
da57dbcd-01c8-488d-a80e-bc2056ea82c2	6fd89164-e8b5-4baf-bbf9-f89c127e8e00	In the case of a reward contract, when does acceptance occur?	MULTIPLE_CHOICE	1	7	["When the offeree promises to find the lost item.", "When the offeree informs the offeror of their intention to perform.", "Upon the successful performance of the requested act.", "When the offeror gives the reward."]	Upon the successful performance of the requested act.	In a unilateral contract, like a reward, acceptance occurs when the requested act is performed.	2025-11-27 11:18:04.366067	2025-11-27 11:18:04.366069
cfebba62-74fb-4659-9899-eb9847efca6e	6fd89164-e8b5-4baf-bbf9-f89c127e8e00	How does the case of *Carlill v Carbolic Smoke Ball Co* illustrate a unilateral contract?	MULTIPLE_CHOICE	1	8	["It involved a promise of payment upon selling a product.", "The company promised payment upon the performance of an act (using the product).", "It was based on mutual promises between two parties.", "It involved a counter-offer that was accepted."]	The company promised payment upon the performance of an act (using the product).	*Carlill v Carbolic Smoke Ball Co* is a classic unilateral contract case where the company promised payment upon the act of using their product.	2025-11-27 11:18:04.366085	2025-11-27 11:18:04.366087
55bcd07c-a1b0-4921-8d07-c5287056c57e	6fd89164-e8b5-4baf-bbf9-f89c127e8e00	What principle was suggested by Lord Denning regarding the revocation of unilateral offers in *Errington v Errington*?	MULTIPLE_CHOICE	1	9	["Unilateral offers can be revoked at any time.", "Performance must begin before a revocation can be effective.", "Once performance has started, the offer cannot be revoked.", "Revocation is effective without communication."]	Once performance has started, the offer cannot be revoked.	Lord Denning suggested that in a unilateral contract, once the offeree has begun performance, the offeror cannot revoke the offer.	2025-11-27 11:18:04.366103	2025-11-27 11:18:04.366105
bc800743-c6ad-4b78-984d-28370cf39ca9	c6909798-ac29-4f72-902d-8e42ee58fdde	Which type of machine learning involves the model being trained on a labeled dataset?	MULTIPLE_CHOICE	1	0	["Supervised Learning", "Unsupervised Learning", "Reinforcement Learning", "Deep Learning"]	Supervised Learning	In supervised learning, the model is provided with labeled data which helps it learn the mapping between input and output.	2025-11-27 12:30:23.147994	2025-11-27 12:30:23.148003
2e315738-ca05-4339-86cd-ba9c045c89ba	c6909798-ac29-4f72-902d-8e42ee58fdde	Why might precision be a more suitable performance metric than accuracy in certain situations?	MULTIPLE_CHOICE	1	1	["Because precision considers both true positives and false negatives.", "Because precision is more intuitive than accuracy.", "Because precision focuses on the relevance of the retrieved results, especially in imbalanced datasets.", "Because precision is always higher than accuracy."]	Because precision focuses on the relevance of the retrieved results, especially in imbalanced datasets.	Precision is important when false positives are more critical to avoid, such as in disease detection where correct identification of positive cases is crucial.	2025-11-27 12:30:23.148022	2025-11-27 12:30:23.148023
56c5d820-ca24-4a1e-a4eb-62fc45c0250a	c6909798-ac29-4f72-902d-8e42ee58fdde	Which algorithm would likely be the best choice for a complex task like image recognition?	MULTIPLE_CHOICE	1	2	["Linear Regression", "Logistic Regression", "Decision Trees", "Neural Networks"]	Neural Networks	Neural networks, particularly deep learning models, excel at complex tasks such as image and speech recognition due to their ability to capture intricate patterns.	2025-11-27 12:30:23.148035	2025-11-27 12:30:23.148036
12eb4e25-a6dc-4e8a-bd2c-4846e19f6be5	c6909798-ac29-4f72-902d-8e42ee58fdde	What is overfitting in the context of machine learning?	MULTIPLE_CHOICE	1	3	["When a model performs poorly on training data but well on unseen data.", "When a model performs well on training data but poorly on unseen data.", "When a model performs equally well on both training and unseen data.", "When a model stops learning from the data."]	When a model performs well on training data but poorly on unseen data.	Overfitting occurs when a model learns the training data too well, including noise and details, which hampers its performance on new, unseen data.	2025-11-27 12:30:23.148048	2025-11-27 12:30:23.148049
da0ee0a7-b91e-45a4-a551-b1d7638806b2	c6909798-ac29-4f72-902d-8e42ee58fdde	Which study strategy is considered more effective for retaining information?	MULTIPLE_CHOICE	1	4	["Passive reading", "Cramming the night before", "Active learning and practice", "Listening to lectures only"]	Active learning and practice	Active learning and practice involve engaging with the material through problem-solving and application, which improves retention and understanding.	2025-11-27 12:30:23.148058	2025-11-27 12:30:23.148059
53719e0a-331a-4a7c-9355-dce1a4bf7c02	c6909798-ac29-4f72-902d-8e42ee58fdde	What is a common technique to prevent overfitting?	MULTIPLE_CHOICE	1	5	["Using a linear model", "Cross-validation", "Increasing the model complexity", "Reducing the dataset size"]	Cross-validation	Cross-validation helps ensure that the model's performance is consistent across different subsets of the data, mitigating the risk of overfitting.	2025-11-27 12:30:23.148069	2025-11-27 12:30:23.148069
914d74dd-ba68-4d0d-9a9d-d053ebf9221a	c6909798-ac29-4f72-902d-8e42ee58fdde	Which of the following is NOT a type of machine learning?	MULTIPLE_CHOICE	1	6	["Supervised Learning", "Unsupervised Learning", "Assisted Learning", "Reinforcement Learning"]	Assisted Learning	Assisted Learning is not a recognized category in the field; the primary types are Supervised, Unsupervised, and Reinforcement Learning.	2025-11-27 12:30:23.148078	2025-11-27 12:30:23.148079
9919a6b1-af3e-4f1c-a5ef-69444779e534	c6909798-ac29-4f72-902d-8e42ee58fdde	In the context of machine learning, what does regularization help with?	MULTIPLE_CHOICE	1	7	["Improving model accuracy on the test data", "Increasing the complexity of the model", "Reducing overfitting by penalizing complex models", "Ensuring the model trains faster"]	Reducing overfitting by penalizing complex models	Regularization adds a penalty for larger coefficients to the loss function, discouraging overly complex models that are prone to overfitting.	2025-11-27 12:30:23.148088	2025-11-27 12:30:23.148089
5f577fd7-9d08-4d0b-bb52-6d65e22d6ad4	c6909798-ac29-4f72-902d-8e42ee58fdde	Which machine learning algorithm is best for handling a large number of features in a dataset?	MULTIPLE_CHOICE	1	8	["Decision Trees", "Random Forests", "Support Vector Machines", "Logistic Regression"]	Support Vector Machines	Support Vector Machines are particularly effective in high-dimensional spaces and can handle a large number of features efficiently.	2025-11-27 12:30:23.148097	2025-11-27 12:30:23.148098
a9f7d25c-3115-4bd3-a23b-3140ea8301a9	c6909798-ac29-4f72-902d-8e42ee58fdde	Why is it important to balance study with rest before exams?	MULTIPLE_CHOICE	1	9	["To avoid having too much free time", "Because a tired mind is less effective at retaining information", "To ensure you have something to do in between study sessions", "Because rest is more important than study"]	Because a tired mind is less effective at retaining information	Rest is crucial for cognitive processing and memory consolidation, making it important to balance study with adequate rest.	2025-11-27 12:30:23.148108	2025-11-27 12:30:23.148108
b3226690-b201-4bf7-94b3-d2b819586eb8	ee4297bc-ae19-4e8e-b53e-8c207fda4177	What core role do lawyers play according to the lecture?	MULTIPLE_CHOICE	1	0	["Advocates for the judicial system", "Interpreters and appliers of the law", "Intermediaries between society and state institutions", "Arbitrators in legal disputes"]	Intermediaries between society and state institutions	Lawyers serve as bridges between the public and judicial systems.	2025-11-27 17:20:03.950923	2025-11-27 17:20:03.950923
3f11f29d-5b53-45be-a81f-8420dedae307	ee4297bc-ae19-4e8e-b53e-8c207fda4177	Which of the following is NOT a component of the course grading criteria?	MULTIPLE_CHOICE	1	1	["Class Participation", "Assignments and Quizzes", "Mid-term Exam", "Research Paper"]	Research Paper	The grading criteria include class participation, assignments, and exams but not a research paper.	2025-11-27 17:20:03.950923	2025-11-27 17:20:03.950923
b2662f51-037d-410e-8db2-1f1fa984a17e	ee4297bc-ae19-4e8e-b53e-8c207fda4177	How are mid-term exams conducted in this course?	MULTIPLE_CHOICE	1	2	["Multiple choice exam", "Written essay", "Presentation", "Oral examination"]	Presentation	The mid-term exam is conducted as a presentation.	2025-11-27 17:20:03.950923	2025-11-27 17:20:03.950923
561db250-f17b-4449-8eea-ab77250bb763	ee4297bc-ae19-4e8e-b53e-8c207fda4177	What percentage of the final grade is determined by class participation?	MULTIPLE_CHOICE	1	3	["5%", "10%", "15%", "20%"]	10%	Class participation accounts for 10% of the final grade.	2025-11-27 17:20:03.950923	2025-11-27 17:20:03.950923
bf553366-f5d5-4c50-ae3b-bad2d3b11cdc	cb9182ef-a171-4f5b-8873-3fe97087c298	What concept did Albert Venn Dicey emphasize in the Western legal tradition?	MULTIPLE_CHOICE	1	7	["The importance of customary law", "The rule of law and equality before the law", "The supremacy of religious law", "The necessity of jury trials"]	The rule of law and equality before the law	Albert Venn Dicey emphasized the rule of law and the concept of equality before the law in the Western legal tradition.	2025-11-27 17:35:05.444024	2025-11-27 17:35:05.444024
ab0a3c55-2935-4875-bab6-6e905523e201	cb9182ef-a171-4f5b-8873-3fe97087c298	Which legal system is primarily found in the United States and the UK?	MULTIPLE_CHOICE	1	8	["Civil law", "Common law", "Religious law", "Tribal law"]	Common law	Common law is the primary legal system in the United States and the UK, based on judicial decisions and case law.	2025-11-27 17:35:05.444024	2025-11-27 17:35:05.444024
38415a44-7221-48ca-a072-69fddb7438db	cb9182ef-a171-4f5b-8873-3fe97087c298	What does civil law rely on to provide clarity and consistency in legal rulings?	MULTIPLE_CHOICE	1	9	["Oral traditions", "Case precedents", "Codified statutes and legal codes", "Discretion of judges"]	Codified statutes and legal codes	Civil law systems rely on codified statutes and legal codes to ensure clarity and consistency in legal rulings.	2025-11-27 17:35:05.444024	2025-11-27 17:35:05.444024
